    "where I S is subscription income (if any) and the second term is total digital ad revenue.",
    "Specifically, z i denotes the number of ads (in expectation) that can be presented to user i and δ is revenue per ad.",
    "Under social media model in the next section, we assume that there is no subscription income, δ is exogenously given, and z i is proportional to the number of shares of posts that individual i engages in.",
    "Therefore, 1 0 z i di will be proportional to the total engagement of content on social media, incentivizing the platform to maximize engagement or shares.",
